==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Urrhodin
<hw>Ur*rho"din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>uro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a rose.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld>
<def>Indigo red, a product of the decomposition, or oxidation, of
indican. It is sometimes found in the sediment of pathological urines.
It is soluble in ether or alcohol, giving the solution a beautiful red
color. Also called <altname>indigrubin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urry</ent>⟦br⟧
